NHL STANLEY CUP FINALS: KINGS v DEVILS
June 3, 2012
Matt Greene
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   


  THE MODERATOR:   Questions for Matt Greene.   
   
 Q.   When you first came in, I'm assuming he was brutally honest to begin with, did you have to get used to that, or it's a good coach?  
MATT GREENE:   No.   He tells you what he thinks.   He tells you what you need to do better, what you're doing right.   That's what you need.   That's what a lot of guys needed on this team.   It's worked out well for us.   
   
 Q.   You talked last night about wanting to improve.   Why is that?   
MATT GREENE:   I think the forecheck is great right now.   It's getting a lot of things done for them that they want to get done.   We want more pressure in the offensive zone.   
   
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT